               <interp inst="t18350202-646" type="date" value="18350202"></interp>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t18350202-646-charge-1" targOrder="Y" targets="def1-646-18350202 t18350202-646-offence-1 t18350202-646-verdict-1"></join>
               <p>646. <persName id="def1-646-18350202" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def1-646-18350202" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-646-18350202" type="age" value="18"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-646-18350202" type="surname" value="HEWITT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-646-18350202" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">JOSEPH HEWITT</hi>
                  </persName> was indicted<rs id="t18350202-646-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18350202-646-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18350202-646-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="simpleLarceny"></interp> for stealing, on the <rs id="t18350202-cd-146" type="crimeDate">
                        <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18350202-646-offence-1 t18350202-cd-146"></join>19th of Ja<lb></lb>nuary</rs>, 1 handkerchief, value 3<hi rend="italic">s</hi>., the goods of <persName id="t18350202-name-1049" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18350202-name-1049" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350202-name-1049" type="surname" value="MARTIN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350202-name-1049" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18350202-646-offence-1 t18350202-name-1049"></join>Thomas Martin</persName>.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18350202-name-1050" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18350202-name-1050" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350202-name-1050" type="surname" value="POTTER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350202-name-1050" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM POTTER</persName>
                  </hi>. I am an apprentice to Mr. Thomas Martin, of Tooley-street, Borough, a pawnbroker. On the 19th of January, in the afternoon, I was directed to the end of the shop by somebody, and saw the prisoner drawing his hand from his pocket, as if he had put something into</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183502020178"></xptr>
               <p>it, and then he looked at some other goods—I laid hold of him, and he im<lb></lb>mediately produced this handkerchief from his pocket—it had hung at up in the shop—I detained him till the officer came, and then gave him into custody.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. PHILLIPS</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> How long was it before the offi<lb></lb>cer came? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> About ten minutes—I held him all the time—he did not tell me the handkerchief was falling, and he caught it to prevent its falling—a person at the door said, "What has he done?" and then he said, "The handkerchief fell down, and I picked it up." I had hold of him at the time the officer came—he did not attempt to escape—there was only one person in the shop, but four or five in the boxes—the person in the shop was a stranger—he could not see what he was doing, without turning round to look at him.</p>
               <p>(<hi rend="italic">Property produced and sworn to.</hi>)</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> I saw some yellow handkerchiefs hanging up, and went in and looked at than—I saw some more hanging near the counter—I went to look at those, and they came down in my hand—I said, "Here is one of your handkerchiefs come down"—he said, "I know all about it, you wanted to steal it"—I said, "I have not stolen it, and am not going to run away"—he said, "I will take good care you shall not," and he gave me in charge.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">JURY</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">to</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">WILLIAM POTTER</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Was the handkerchief out of sight till it was given to you? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes, his jacket was buttoned—I saw his hand withdrawn from his pocket, it had nothing in it—when I laid bold of him he gave me the handkerchief from his pocket.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18350202-name-1051" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18350202-name-1051" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350202-name-1051" type="surname" value="STORY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350202-name-1051" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN STORY</persName>
                  </hi>. I am an officer. I found the prisoner in the shop—Pot<lb></lb>ter had the handkerchief in his hand—the prisoner was standing quietly there—he certainly denied it.</p>
               <p>(Mary Guest—Thomas Hadlam, leather-dyer, Camberwell; and James Drew, leather-dyer; gave the prisoner a good character.)</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="largeCaps">
                     <rs id="t18350202-646-verdict-1" type="verdictDescription">
                        <interp inst="t18350202-646-verdict-1" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350202-646-verdict-1" type="verdictSubcategory" value="no_subcategory"></interp>GUILTY</rs>
                  </hi>. Aged 18.—
<rs id="t18350202-646-punishment-133" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18350202-646-punishment-133" type="punishmentCategory" value="imprison"></interp>
